    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for Ghost Ride the WHIP hinges on aggressive exploitation of favorable pitching matchups, specifically against Fedde and the Colorado staff. Our highest-rated play of the day is **Corbin Carroll** (80.12), who remains an absolute must-start against Scherzer. While the veteran pitcher can still be tricky, the combination of **Corbin Carroll**\u2019s elite speed profile and his strong xwOBA gives him a massive ceiling. **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) and **James Wood** (71.32) follow closely behind; **Tyler Soderstrom** benefits heavily from the 5.60 xERA of Fedde, while **James Wood** leverages a premium leadoff spot to maximize his plate appearance volume despite a slight efficiency penalty due to the opposing catcher's pop time.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Seiya Suzuki** (52.23) out of the outfield rotation. **Seiya Suzuki** hovered near the \"Strong\" start threshold, but the 3.68 xERA of Peralta combined with a mediocre BvP history pushed him just behind the likes of **Giancarlo Stanton** (60.51) and **Mickey Moniak** (64.31). **Mickey Moniak** specifically secured his spot by maximizing the park factors against Sheehan. Meanwhile, we are keeping a close watch on **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (58.79) and **Jose Caballero** (67.61); although both are currently slotted into the lineup, the \"Wind In\" advisory at their venue introduces a volatility risk that could suppress their power outcomes. We are comfortable with this configuration as we prioritize the stolen base potential inherent in the matchups for **Brice Turang** and **Jose Caballero**, banking on the slow deliveries of their opposing hurlers to keep our team total competitive.",
